text: SK Tallinna Sport is a defunct Estonian football club, founded in 1912 and then re-established in 2003. The club won nine domestic league titles before Estonia became a part of Soviet Union. The club also played bandy in the interwar years, becoming Estonian champions of this sport eleven times in the 1920s and 1930s. At last the club played in the III Liiga (Pőhi), northern zone of Estonian Third league, fourth tier of Estonian football pyramid.
